HEADWORD: Ectoderm
<hw>Ec"to*derm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ecto-</ets> +
<ets>-derm</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The outer
layer of the blastoderm; epiblast.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The external
skin or outer layer of an animal or plant, this being formed in an
animal from the epiblast. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Blastoderm</er>.</def></p>

